      "description": "A review system with product and seller reviews, ratings, customer/vendor/admin API routes, and workflows.",
      "dependencies": [],
      "registryDependencies": [],
      "docs": "## Reviews Block Configuration\n\nAdd the review module to your `medusa-config.ts`:\n\n```ts\nmodules: [\n  {\n    resolve: './modules/reviews',\n  },\n]\n```\n\nThis block provides:\n- **Review Module** - Data model for product and seller reviews with ratings (1-5)\n- **Links** - Connects reviews to customers, orders, products, and sellers\n- **Workflows** - Create, update, and delete review workflows with validation\n- **API Routes** - Admin, store (customer), and vendor (seller) endpoints\n- **Subscriber** - Handles review deletion on remove-review-request events\n\n### API Endpoints\n\n**Admin:**\n- `GET /admin/reviews` - List all reviews\n- `GET /admin/reviews/:id` - Get review by ID\n\n**Store (Customer):**\n- `GET /store/reviews` - List customer's reviews\n- `POST /store/reviews` - Create a review\n- `GET /store/reviews/:id` - Get review by ID\n- `POST /store/reviews/:id` - Update a review\n- `DELETE /store/reviews/:id` - Delete a review\n\n**Vendor (Seller):**\n- `GET /vendor/sellers/me/reviews` - List seller's reviews\n- `GET /vendor/sellers/me/reviews/:id` - Get review by ID\n- `POST /vendor/sellers/me/reviews/:id` - Respond to a review (seller_note)",
